1. To retrieve the current thread from JVM
Thread currentthread = Thread.currentThread();
currentthread.getName();

2. Set the thread priority
Thread Object
obj.setPriority(priority_type);

1. MAX_PRIORITY - 10
2. NORM_PRIORITY - 5(default for any thread)
3. MIN_PRIORITY - 1

3. Yield() Method - Is a static method of Thread class and it can stop the currently executing thread and
will give a chance to other waiting threads of the same priority. If in case there are no waiting threads
or if all the waiting threads have low priority then the same thread will continue its execution.

